In Vegas for the weekend and looking for off the strip eats. This little restaurant is located off Lake Mead Pkwy and Water in Henderson, NV.  Decor is small town cafe tables and chairs with lots of metal tin signs hung on the walls. The food does not disappoint with generous portions at a great price. I opted for the French toast with bacon and over easy eggs while my son had a breakfast burrito with chili. We enjoyed both dishes and neither of us could finish the portion size. Recommended for those looking for a small local restaurant when in Vegas.

